The '''Lankorians''' were an alien species native to the planet [[Lankor VI]]. They were bipedal, with skinny arms and a head shaped like a sugar-loaf. Their planet was temperate and had had established a feudal-level civilization by the period of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]. Their planet came under the control of the [[Flight Unlimited Group]], an Imperial-aligned corporation. While the Lankorians were largely ambivalent about FUG control, it did give them access to rudimentary interstellar trade.<ref name="Le facteur X">''{{CasusBelliCite|115|Le facteur X}}''</ref>

The Lankorians established a number of towns, including [[Rham'Dhaam]].<ref name="Le facteur X" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Lankorians appeared in an article in [[Casus Belli (magazine)|''Casus Belli'']], a French roleplaying magazine. The adventure revolved around a group of Rebel characters traveling [[Time travel/Legends|back in time]] to the period of the [[Great Sith War/Legends|Great Sith War]].<ref name="Le facteur X" />

